---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Worlds — DID One" description="Different worlds, different systems of work, same protocol.">
  <main class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="badge">Many Worlds</div>
      <h1>Different worlds. Different systems of work.</h1>
      <p class="lede">The world decides the work. The protocol decides the trust. The base decides the truth.</p>
      <div class="panel">
        <pre class="code-card">0  Void
1  Identity Core World
2  Relation World
3  Movement World
4  Stability World
5  Governance World
6  Enterprise World
7  Social World
8  Commerce World
9  Globalization World
10 Federation World
11 Agentic World
12 Real World
13 R&D World
14 Excellence World
15 Exploration World
16 Multiversal World</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="card"><h3>Different work</h3><p>Governance, enterprise, social, commerce, research, games, books, movies, and agents have different operating patterns.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Same protocol</h3><p>DID, VC, wallet, AuthZEN, block, receipt, trust chain, audit, and recovery bind every world.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Open at the end</h3><p>Worlds can specialize without breaking identity, proof, recovery, or backward verification.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
